    <h2 class="section-title">Context</h2>
    <div class="case-study-prose">
      <p>
        HabitualOS is an open-source agentic AI platform — a monorepo of specialized agents
        and shared infrastructure designed to apply AI where behavior change is hardest:
        in the small moments of daily life.
      </p>
      <p>
        The core question driving it: how do you build AI agents that actually support human
        judgment rather than replace it? The answer that emerged through building and living
        with these apps — constrained agents are more trustworthy. Narrow scope, explicit
        handoffs, typed signals instead of freeform prompting.
      </p>
      <p>
        Five apps now run on the platform, each testing a different dimension of daily life:
        personal productivity, health and wellness, relationships, creative practice, and
        financial habits. They're not prototypes — they're production tools I use every day.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

